    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is accepted because ASTM F1717 defines a single standardized configuration and the COU is explicitly scoped to that configuration. Quantitative output comparison metrics (E/uval < 1.96, relative error < 10%) are satisfied for all three primary QoIs across both laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for the stated COU.",
